#X text 30 22 A "filter sweep" is a common technique in Subtractive Synthesis and it consists of using an LFO to modulate the filter frequency. Below we have a sawtooth source being filtered by [vcf~]. The filter is controlled by a LFO at 0.2 Hz and the frequency range is from 500 to 2500 hz., f 65;
